  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this project is to identify brain mechanisms by which Noninvasive brain
      stimulation (NIBS) could decrease hyperphagia. The investigators will synchronously deliver
      NIBS and measure brain activity in a randomized, crossover, sham-controlled, fully blind
      study. This work will reveal brain mechanisms to reduce hyperphagia and may contribute to new
      therapeutic avenues to treat this eating disorder.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
